#simply run a docker compose up command to bring up the entire application stack.  
This is easier to implement run and maintain. As all changes are always stored in the docker compose configuration file. 
It is only applicable to running containers on a single Docker Host 
# if you need to set up a complex application running multiple services a better way to do it is to use DOCKER COMPOSE.
docker compose is a YAML format
